headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 35 points and the NBA-leading Cleveland Cavaliers beat the Indiana Pacers 127-117 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: NBA-leading Cavaliers end Pacers' 6-game winning streak with a 127-117 victory

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 32 points and Jalen Williams had 24 to lead the Oklahoma City Thunder to a 118-102 win over a Philadelphia 76ers team missing three All-Stars on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scores 32 as the Thunder beat the short-handed 76ers 118-102

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored a season-high 43 points and the Atlanta Hawks overcame Devin Booker's 35 points to beat Phoenix 122-117 on Tuesday night and snap the Suns' three-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores season-high 43 points as Hawks continue home dominance over Booker-led Suns, 122-117

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Trey Murphy III scored 32 points and Zion Williamson added 21 as the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Chicago Bulls 119-113 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murphy and Williamson carry the Pelicans to a 119-113 win over the Bulls

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 30 points, 13 assists and 11 rebounds for his 50th career triple-double as the Milwaukee Bucks beat Sacramento 130-115 on Tuesday night to snap the Kings’ seven-game win streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo gets 50th career triple-double as Bucks win 130-115 to end Kings' 7-game win streak

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored 32 of his season-high 45 points in the first half and led the Denver Nuggets to a 118-99 victory over the Dallas Mavericks on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jamal Murray scores 32 of his season-high 45 points in the 1st half as Nuggets beat Mavs 118-99

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Cam Johnson returned from a five-game absence with a right ankle sprain and scored 24 points in the Brooklyn Nets' 132-114 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cam Johnson returns from ankle injury and has 24 points in Nets' 132-114 win at Portland
